      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MY BREAD ROLL (1) goes very well at this course having never missed the frame including four wins and three placings. Hit the frame latest (22.55) when second at this track in a Grade 5. Has the ability and looks a key chance here. LOCHINVAR GRACE (7) goes very well at the distance with two wins and a placing from five starts. Scored by 1.3 lengths last time (23.04) in a Grade 5 over 400m at this track. Makes strong appeal on best. LAURIE'S FERRARI (3) stalked the lead from a low draw and fought on well to finish 3 lengths back in third (22.46) at Maitland in a Grade 5 over 400m. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from three starts. Can feature again. IT'S A TEASE (2) is not to be discarded.",
